  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0bb0\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0b95 \u0b95\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb9\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bbe",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Policy resolution should be implemented regarding civil servants - Nalaka Kodahewa",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The government has yet to come up with a formal plan to address the crisis, with negotiations to seek IMF assistance pending finalisation.",
        "In addition to the demand in the government service, the internal staffing is intensifying the government expenditure day by day.",
        "Former Minister Prof. Nalaka Kodaheva said that the government should implement a policy decision regarding government servants.",
        "He mentioned the above in a discussion organized by the students of Kelani University on the theme 'What is the solution to practical crises'.",
        "Everyone knows that if there is to be a short-term solution to the problems that have arisen in the practice, they will have to get government loans, and that is what the government is hoping for in its negotiations with the International Monetary Fund.",
        "No company will give loans without presenting a plan to repay the government loans. Therefore, a long-term plan implementation type of solution is necessary.",
        "The government should pay more attention to the four main issues of earning foreign exchange, limiting foreign expenditure, increasing national income, and controlling national expenditure.",
        "Due opportunity has been provided to rectify the historical mistakes and find a sustainable solution to the current economic crisis. Another problem is that the Parliament and the people do not give permission to take important decisions.",
        "The 2021 budget gap of 12 percent of the GDP is a huge problem. The money printing to complete the budget while not being able to pay the existing debt has intensified the crisis. The government should pay more attention to national expenditure control.",
        "Government expenditure control policy should be seen as aimed at cost containment and elimination of fraud rather than cost reduction.",
        "Government expenditure in 2021 is Rs 3,521 billion, of which Rs 2,748 billion is estimated as incremental expenditure. Only Rs 1,115 billion is spent on salaries of government employees. 1048 billion has been disbursed towards government loans taken.",
        "Out of the 420 development projects owned by the government, only 52 projects are beneficial to the government. On the other hand, the government institutions and corporations operating in the industry are another factor in the economic crisis.",
        "The Sri Lanka Electricity Board faced Nt214 billion, the Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation Nt82.2 billion and Sri Lankan Airlines Nt170.7 billion.",
        "There are currently 1,402,000 civil servants, 792,000 in ministries and departments, 390,000 in regional and local councils, and 220,000 in government projects.",
        "It is paradoxical that the government income is limited to 80 percent while the total expenditure is 1115 billion.",
        "There are more than enough civil servants. He said that the government should take actionable decisions regarding the civil servants in the future. He said that the government has failed to find a solution that originated in the social structure."
      ],
